com.metreeca.rest.services

Interface Engine

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DatastoreEngine

    public interface Engine
    Model-driven storage engine.

    Manages storage transactions, performs storage-specific shape/payload tasks and handles model-driven CRUD actions on resources and containers.

    • Method Detail

      • engine

        static Supplier<Engine> engine()
        Retrieves the default engine factory.
        Returns:
        the default engine factory, which throws an exception reporting the service as undefined

      • exec

        default void exec(Runnable task)
        Executes a task within a storage transaction.

        If a transaction is not already active on the underlying storage, begins one and commits it on successful task completion; if the task throws an exception, the transaction is rolled back and the exception rethrown; in either case, no action is taken if the transaction was already terminated inside the task.

        Falls back to plain task execution if transactions are not supported by this engine.

        Parameters:
        task - the task to be executed
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if task is null

      • exec

        <R> R exec(Supplier<R> task)
        Executes a task within a storage transaction.

        If a transaction is not already active on the underlying storage, begins one and commits it on successful task completion; if the task throws an exception, the transaction is rolled back and the exception rethrown; in either case, no action is taken if the transaction was already terminated inside the task.

        Falls back to plain task execution if transactions are not supported by this engine.

        Type Parameters:
        R - the type of the value returned by the task
        Parameters:
        task - the task to be executed
        Returns:
        the value returned by task
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if task is null or returns a null value

      • trim

        <M extends Message<M>> Result<M,Failure> trim(M message)
        Trims the message payload.

        Rewrites the engine-specific message payload retaining only the subset compatible with the envelope of the message shape.

        Type Parameters:
        M - the type of message
        Parameters:
        message - the message whose engine-specific payload is to be trimmed
        Returns:
        a value providing access to the given message with an updated payload, if its engine-specific payload is well-formed and compatible with its shape; an error providing access to a failure possibly containing a validation trace, otherwise
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if message is null

      • validate

        <M extends Message<M>> Result<M,Failure> validate(M message)
        Validates the message payload.

        Validates the engine-specific message payload against the message shape.

        Type Parameters:
        M - the type of message
        Parameters:
        message - the message whose engine-specific payload is to be validated
        Returns:
        a value providing access to message, if its engine-specific payload is well-formed and compatible with its shape; an error providing access to a failure possibly containing a validation trace, otherwise
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if message is null
